            <p>שלם
                    <lb/>
                    ומתיה ברה
                    <lb/>
                     אתת מתיה וברה
                </p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="jeru0045.translation" corresp="#jeru0045.transcription">
            <p>Shalom and Matya, her son. Matya's wife and her son.</p>
         </div>
      <div type="edition" subtype="transcription_segmented"><p><w xml:id="jeru0045-1" xml:lang="arc">שלם</w> <w xml:id="jeru0045-2" xml:lang="arc">ומתיה</w> <w xml:id="jeru0045-3" xml:lang="arc">ברה</w> <w xml:id="jeru0045-4" xml:lang="arc">אתת</w> <w xml:id="jeru0045-5" xml:lang="arc">מתיה</w> <w xml:id="jeru0045-6" xml:lang="arc">וברה</w> </p>
</div>
</body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Ossuary has inner ledge on two sides, low feet, red wash and flat lid. First two lines of inscription appear on the chest's front side; last line appears on the lid. שלם is a contraction of the name שלמציון and מתיה is a contraction of מתתיה. The husband/father of the two, sharing a name with his son, appears to be buried in a second ossuary in the same tomb.</p>
         </div>
